parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the CVT transmission can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
The failure of the axle can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or injuries.
The shifter plate guide issue can cause the key to become stuck in the ignition, leading to inconvenience and potential safety risks.
The failure of the rear wheel bearings can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or injuries.
The brake malfunction can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or injuries.
The failure of the ignition system can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, leading to safety risks and inconvenience.
symptoms: The key gets stuck in the ignition

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden shattering of the sunroof can cause injury, distraction, and loss of control while driving.
symptoms: The sunroof breaks suddenly without any impact
and fragments fall into the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the VDC system can cause loss of control, accidents, and safety risks, especially in slippery conditions.
symptoms: The vehicle yaws or sways excessively
the VDC system applies brakes unexpectedly
and the traction control light is illuminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the battery or electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, leading to safety risks and inconvenience.
symptoms: the horn only works when the steering wheel is turned
and the vehicle's electrical systems malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine or performance systems can cause loss of power, stalling, and safety risks while driving.
symptoms: the check oil light is illuminated
and the vehicle consumes excessive oil.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the wheel bearings can cause loss of control, accidents, and safety risks, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: The wheel bearings fail while in motion

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the infotainment system can cause distraction and inconvenience while driving.
symptoms: Preprogrammed phone numbers sometimes work and sometimes give an error message
and the system is not available while the vehicle is in motion.
